This TikZ code produces a diagram illustrating wave refraction at a deep-shallow water boundary. Key features include:
- Parallel ripple lines approaching the boundary at an angle
- Longer wavelength ($\lambda_1$) in deep water (blue)
- Shorter wavelength ($\lambda_2$) in shallow water (red)
- Ray direction arrows bending toward the normal (dashed line)
- Explicit wavelength labels showing $\lambda_1 > \lambda_2$
- Clearly labeled "Deep water" and "Shallow water" regions

The diagram uses:
- Blue lines for deep water wave fronts
- Red lines for shallow water wave fronts
- Green double arrows for wavelength indicators
- Thick direction arrows showing wave propagation
- Dashed vertical line for the normal
- Horizontal boundary at y=0

