This TikZ code produces four horizontally aligned nucleus pairs showing decay processes:
- Each nucleus is represented by a circle containing proton (p) and neutron (n) counts
- Arrows labeled with decay types connect initial (left) and final (right) nuclei
- Alpha decay reduces protons by 2 and neutrons by 2
- Beta-minus increases protons by 1 and decreases neutrons by 1
- Beta-plus decreases protons by 1 and increases neutrons by 1
- Gamma decay shows identical nuclei with no changes
All labels use exact notation from the description (α, β⁻, β⁺, γ). The layout uses consistent spacing with 3cm horizontal separation between nuclei and 2cm vertical separation between decay types.

